During a press briefing aboard Air Force One, President Trump addressed various topics including Susan Rice's unmasking of officials in his campaign, the response to Hurricane Irma in Florida and the Virgin Islands, the Iran nuclear deal, outreach to Democrats, tax reform, climate change, the Federal Reserve, and North Korea. The President expressed his disapproval of Rice's actions, praised the response efforts in Florida, and stated that the Iran deal is one of the worst deals ever made. He also mentioned his willingness to work with Democrats to get things passed, expressed confidence in Secretary of the Treasury Steven Mnuchin and National Economic Council Director Gary Cohn, and discussed his conversation with Senator Tim Scott regarding diversity in his administration. The President mentioned his upcoming trip to the United Nations, plans for tax reform, and his thoughts on climate change. He also mentioned the possibility of visiting China, Japan, South Korea, Vietnam, and the Philippines in November.